{
	"components": [
		{
			"id": "input",
			"provider": "webhook",
			"name": "Webhook",
			"config": {},
			"ui": {
				"position": {
					"x": 0,
					"y": 150
				},
				"nodeType": "default",
				"formDataValid": false
			}
		},
		{
			"id": "review_agent",
			"provider": "agent_rocketride",
			"name": "RocketRide Wave",
			"config": {
				"agent_description": "Preflight deploy-readiness reviewer",
				"instructions": [
					"You are Preflight's review pipeline. Each request is a JSON object: {review_id, project_id, repo_url, kind}.",
					"Protocol \u2014 follow exactly:",
					"1. Clone the repo with the git tool (read-only).",
					"2. With the python tool, list *.py files and extract: import edges between repo files, os.environ/os.getenv reads (name + line), hardcoded credential literals (sk_live_/whsec_/AKIA/ghp_ prefixes or SECRET/TOKEN/API_KEY = '<16+ chars>'), and the prod env manifest keys (deploy/prod.env, prod.env, or .env.production). Changed files = .preflight-changed manifest if present, else all files.",
					"3. With the neo4j tool, MERGE the graph: (Project {id})-[:HAS_FILE]->(File {key: project_id + '#' + path}), (File)-[:IMPORTS]->(File), (File)-[:READS {line}]->(EnvVar {key: project_id + '#' + name}), (EnvVar)-[:SET_IN]->(Env {name:'prod'}) for manifest keys, (Review {id: review_id})-[:CHANGED]->(File). Then run FOUR queries: Q1 blast radius (reverse IMPORTS*1..3 from changed files), Q2 fan-in per changed file (load-bearing when >= 3), Q3 changed files READS EnvVar with no SET_IN prod, Q4 prior Finding nodes ON files within 2 IMPORTS hops. Record findings as (Review)-[:PRODUCED]->(Finding {id: review_id + '#' + n})-[:ON]->(File).",
					"4. Compose findings as JSON objects: {class: missing_env_var|hardcoded_secret|load_bearing_change|model_review, severity: error|warning, confidence, detail (cite file:line and hop counts), file_path, line, graph_evidence: {query, blast, seen_before}}.",
					"5. Only if kind == 'deep': use the daytona tool to run the repo's tests (pip install -r requirements.txt if present, then python -m pytest tests -q) and attach failing output as a finding {class: test_failure, severity: error}; also add at most 2 model_review findings for genuinely new risks you can see in the data.",
					"6. ALWAYS finish by POSTing with the http tool to ${ROCKETRIDE_CALLBACK_URL} with header X-Callback-Key: ${ROCKETRIDE_CALLBACK_KEY} and JSON body {review_id, status: 'complete', blast_radius: <max Q1 count>, model_id: 'llama-3-3-70b@nebius', findings: [...]}. If any earlier step failed, still POST with status 'failed' and findings [].",
					"7. Answer with a one-line summary: '<n> findings; callback <http status>'."
				],
				"max_waves": 12,
				"parameters": {}
			},
			"ui": {
				"position": {
					"x": 0,
					"y": 0
				},
				"nodeType": "default",
				"formDataValid": true
			},
			"input": [
				{
					"lane": "questions",
					"from": "input"
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"id": "nebius_llm",
			"provider": "llm_nebius",
			"name": "Nebius",
			"config": {
				"profile": "llama-3-3-70b",
				"llama-3-3-70b": {
					"apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_NEBIUS_KEY}"
				}
			},
			"ui": {
				"position": {
					"x": 0,
					"y": 0
				},
				"nodeType": "default",
				"formDataValid": true
			},
			"control": [
				{
					"classType": "llm",
					"from": "review_agent"
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"id": "agent_memory",
			"provider": "memory_internal",
			"name": "Memory (Internal)",
			"config": {
				"type": "memory_internal"
			},
			"ui": {
				"position": {
					"x": 0,
					"y": 0
				},
				"nodeType": "default",
				"formDataValid": true
			},
			"control": [
				{
					"classType": "memory",
					"from": "review_agent"
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"id": "git_tool",
			"provider": "tool_git",
			"name": "Git",
			"config": {
				"type": "tool_git",
				"authType": "none",
				"readOnlyMode": false,
				"safeMode": true,
				"repoPath": ""
			},
			"ui": {
				"position": {
					"x": 0,
					"y": 0
				},
				"nodeType": "default",
				"formDataValid": false
			},
			"control": [
				{
					"classType": "tool",
					"from": "review_agent"
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"id": "python_tool",
			"provider": "tool_python",
			"name": "Python",
			"config": {
				"type": "tool_python",
				"timeout": 120,
				"allowedModules": [
					{
						"moduleName": "ast"
					},
					{
						"moduleName": "os"
					},
					{
						"moduleName": "pathlib"
					},
					{
						"moduleName": "re"
					},
					{
						"moduleName": "json"
					}
				]
			},
			"ui": {
				"position": {
					"x": 0,
					"y": 0
				},
				"nodeType": "default",
				"formDataValid": true
			},
			"control": [
				{
					"classType": "tool",
					"from": "review_agent"
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"id": "neo4j_db",
			"provider": "db_neo4j",
			"name": "Neo4J",
			"config": {
				"profile": "default",
				"default": {
					"uri": "${ROCKETRIDE_NEO4J_URI}",
					"database": "d5094fd6",
					"auth_method": "userpass",
					"user": "${ROCKETRIDE_NEO4J_USER}",
					"password": "${ROCKETRIDE_NEO4J_PASS}",
					"allow_execute": true
				}
			},
			"ui": {
				"position": {
					"x": 0,
					"y": 0
				},
				"nodeType": "default",
				"formDataValid": false
			},
			"control": [
				{
					"classType": "tool",
					"from": "review_agent"
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"id": "daytona_tool",
			"provider": "tool_daytona",
			"name": "Daytona",
			"config": {
				"type": "tool_daytona",
				"apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_DAYTONA_KEY}",
				"language": "python",
				"exec_timeout_secs": 180,
				"auto_stop_minutes": 10
			},
			"ui": {
				"position": {
					"x": 0,
					"y": 0
				},
				"nodeType": "default",
				"formDataValid": false
			},
			"control": [
